object.field: Augustus wants to become more sociable.
Augustus wants to learn how to use the computer.
Augustus wants to keep his room clean.

Person needs 24 hour plan of care (May not require supervision at all times but there is someone identified/assigned that is responsible and accessible to the consumer in case of emergency. 24 hour plan of care required for individiual in ICF-MR and waiver eligible individuals);Person requires overnight supervision;Person requires 24 hour awake supervision;
Augustus cannot swim and there is a river of chocolate next door. He has fallen into the river before.

Augustus will take swimming lessons at his day program. In the meantime, he is only allowed in the shallow end of the pool, and he must be accompanied at all times to ensure he does not wander off to the river.
Augustus is allergic to spider bites.
This is a low risk, but staff will check Augustus for indications of a bite. He has an EpiPen if needed.
Augustus eats very quickly, especially when consuming chocolate and sweets.
Staff will watch Augustus when eating and remind him to slow down and chew carefully.
Augustus walks slowly and has some pain in his knees when walking.
Augustus likes to walk with the support of a staff member. He also can use a cane or walker.
Augustus will leave his room and spend 1 hour socializing in the family room each day.
Augustus will visit the family room 4 days per week to meet new people.
Augustus will bring 1 book to share each time he visits the family room 4 days per week.
Augustus will turn on the computer and access the games three times each week with manual assistance.
Augustus will practice his computer skills by playing educational computer games for 30 minutes each session on the computer.
Augustus will make his bed each morning with no more than 1 verbal prompt.
Staff will prompt Augustus to visit the family room.
Staff will bring Augustus to the family room and introduce him to new people.
Staff will help Augustus pick a book that he could share.
Staff will teach Augustus how to turn on the computer and navigate to the games.
Staff will sit with Augustus in case he has questions.
